Before you dive into this bureaucratic labyrinth, a word of advice. The following is a list of [Acts of parliaments](/Act_of_parliament), the formal pronouncements from the [English](/Parliament_of_England), [Scottish](/Parliament_of_Scotland), [Irish](/Parliament_of_Ireland), and later, the [Great Britain](/Parliament_of_Great_Britain) legislative bodies. These are the rules that governed kingdoms, preceding the messy amalgamation you now call the United Kingdom. Don't expect poetry. Expect the grinding gears of history, recorded on parchment.

### Of the [Kingdom of England](/Kingdom_of_England)

A collection of royal statutes and other decrees issued before the concept of Parliament had fully solidified into the institution it would later become. A time of legal experimentation, you could say.

