## 1336 (10 Edw. 3)

The 16th Parliament of King Edward III, which met from 3 March 1337. This session was also traditionally cited as **10 Ed. 3** or **10 E. 3**.

*   **(Pardons, etc.) 10 Edw. 3. Stat. 1**
    *   **c. 1**: A confirmation of former statutes. — repealed by [Statute Law Revision (Ireland) Act 1872](/Statute_Law_Revision_(Ireland)_Act_1872).
    *   **c. 2**: Pardons shall not be granted contrary to the Statute of 2 Edw. III. cap. 2. &#91;a&#93; — repealed for [England and Wales](/England_and_Wales) by [Statute Law Revision Act 1863](/Statute_Law_Revision_Act_1863) ([26 & 27 Vict.](/26_%26_27_Vict.) c. 125) and for [Ireland](/Ireland) by [Statute Law (Ireland) Revision Act 1872](/Statute_Law_(Ireland)_Revision_Act_1872) ([35 & 36 Vict.](/35_%26_36_Vict.) c. 98).
    *   **c. 3**: He that hath a pardon of felony shall find sureties for his good abearing (good behaviour). — repealed for [England and Wales](/England_and_Wales) by [Statute Law Revision Act 1863](/Statute_Law_Revision_Act_1863) ([26 & 27 Vict.](/26_%26_27_Vict.) c. 125) and for [Ireland](/Ireland) by [Statute Law (Ireland) Revision Act 1872](/Statute_Law_(Ireland)_Revision_Act_1872) ([35 & 36 Vict.](/35_%26_36_Vict.) c. 98).
*   **Purveyance, etc. Act 1336** &#91;10&#93; **10 Edw. 3. Stat. 2**
    *   **c. 1**: Things purveyed for the King's House shall be praised (appraised), and tallies made thereof. — repealed for [England and Wales](/England_and_Wales) by [Statute Law Revision Act 1863](/Statute_Law_Revision_Act_1863) ([26 & 27 Vict.](/26_%26_27_Vict.) c. 125) and for [Ireland](/Ireland) by [Statute Law (Ireland) Revision Act 1872](/Statute_Law_(Ireland)_Revision_Act_1872) ([35 & 36 Vict.](/35_%26_36_Vict.) c. 98).
    *   **c. 2**: Of what people inquests in the Marshals Court of the King's House shall be taken. — repealed for [England and Wales](/England_and_Wales) by [Statute Law Revision Act 1863](/Statute_Law_Revision_Act_1863) ([26 & 27 Vict.](/26_%26_27_Vict.) c. 125) and for [Ireland](/Ireland) by [Statute Law (Ireland) Revision Act 1872](/Statute_Law_(Ireland)_Revision_Act_1872) ([35 & 36 Vict.](/35_%26_36_Vict.) c. 98).
    *   **c. 3**: Errors in the Marshals Courts shall be reversed in the King's Bench. — repealed for [England and Wales](/England_and_Wales) by [Statute Law Revision Act 1863](/Statute_Law_Revision_Act_1863) ([26 & 27 Vict.](/26_%26_27_Vict.) c. 125) and for [Ireland](/Ireland) by [Statute Law (Ireland) Revision Act 1872](/Statute_Law_(Ireland)_Revision_Act_1872) ([35 & 36 Vict.](/35_%26_36_Vict.) c. 98).
    *   **c. 4**: The sheriff shall make purveyance for the King's horses. — repealed for [England and Wales](/England_and_Wales) by [Statute Law Revision Act 1863](/Statute_Law_Revision_Act_1863) ([26 & 27 Vict.](/26_%26_27_Vict.) c. 125) and for [Ireland](/Ireland) by [Statute Law (Ireland) Revision Act 1872](/Statute_Law_(Ireland)_Revision_Act_1872) ([35 & 36 Vict.](/35_%26_36_Vict.) c. 98).
    *   **c. 5**: Certain persons shall be appointed to hear the offences of the keepers of the King's horses. — repealed for [England and Wales](/England_and_Wales) by [Statute Law Revision Act 1863](/Statute_Law_Revision_Act_1863) ([26 & 27 Vict.](/26_%26_27_Vict.) c. 125) and for [Ireland](/Ireland) by [Statute Law (Ireland) Revision Act 1872](/Statute_Law_(Ireland)_Revision_Act_1872) ([35 & 36 Vict.](/35_%26_36_Vict.) c. 98).
*   **Statute of Nottingham 10 Edw. 3. Stat. 3 (Sumptuary law)** (*Statutum de Cibariis utendis*): An early attempt to regulate what people could eat, a classic example of legislative overreach. — repealed by [Repeal of Obsolete Statutes Act 1856](/Repeal_of_Obsolete_Statutes_Act_1856) ([19 & 20 Vict.](/19_%26_20_Vict.) c. 64).

