## 1337 (11 Edw. 3)

The 17th Parliament of King Edward III, which met at Westminster from 27 September 1337. This session was also traditionally cited as **11 Ed. 3** or **11 E. 3**.

### Statute made at Westminster.
*   **c. 1 Wool Act 1337**: It shall be a felony to carry any wool out of the realm, until it is otherwise ordained. A protectionist measure with teeth. — repealed by [Repeal of Acts Concerning Importation Act 1822](/Repeal_of_Acts_Concerning_Importation_Act_1822) ([3 Geo. 4](/3_Geo._4). c. 41).
*   **c. 2 [Cloth Act 1337](/Cloth_Act_1337)**: None shall wear any cloth but such as is made in England. — repealed for [England and Wales](/England_and_Wales) by [Statute Law Revision Act 1863](/Statute_Law_Revision_Act_1863) ([26 & 27